@belikewater thanks for the link: https://www.dni.gov/files/ODNI/documents/assessments/Declassified-Assessment-on-COVID-19-Origins.pdf Seems like the same analysis as before, albeit with some cute animal icons this go-around.  We re-learned in this very thorough analysis doc: - It would be so much easier if they could prove wet market origination
- Keeping the lab leak theory in their back pocket to pull out if needed
- China is the preventer of knowledge and truth Politics will determine the final outcome.  And then unredacted documents will be made available through a FOIA request 20 years later disproving whatever claim they make now. :) Degrading by 1%.

Thanks to some good comments and info from: 
@SE_Meyer - https://bit.ly/3e1cVyB
@iceczar  - https://bit.ly/3e2zy5I
@oskar-b  - https://bit.ly/3hVlc8s All of which has persuaded me to revise my forecast and get off the fence. This perhaps also adds to my view - https://bit.ly/3dZ3Qq8 @Chrisp sums it up in this comment; https://bit.ly/2VinwP0. It's all about managing the story ...or more accurately, trying to manage the story within the minefield of politics and national benefit and global geopolitics, IMO.
